main event: A civilian observer reported seeing a round, white, self-luminous object in the sky over Caldwell, New Jersey on May 29, 1952.
interesting points: The object was observed for approximately 30 seconds before disappearing beyond the horizon.,The sighting was the first of an unidentified object in the Caldwell area.,No sound was heard and no vapor trail was observed.,The observer was described as a reliable civilian.,More data is needed to evaluate this sighting.
